   <h2 align="center">Getting Started</h2>
   <hr><br><br>




   To run <b>Standalone</b> or <b>Client</b> application  you have to do follow actions:<br><br><br>
   <b>Windows</b><br><br>
   Menu: Start -&gt; Programs -&gt; Plazma ERP+CRM &lt;version&gt; -&gt; Plazma ERP+CRM<br><br><br>

   or run the command file<br><br>

   <code>plazma.bat</code><br><br><br>

   or run the command<br><br>
   <code>javaw -Djava.library.path="lib\swt\win32" -jar launcher.jar plazma</code><br><br><br>



   <b>Linux</b><br><br>
   run the command file<br><br>

   <code>plazma.sh</code><br><br><br>
   or run the command<br><br>
   <code>java -Djava.library.path="lib/swt/linux-gtk" -jar launcher.jar plazma</code><br><br><br>


   <b>Demo mode</b><br><br>
   To run the program in the demo mode you have to send <code>-demo</code> flag in the command line of launch, for example<br><br>
   <code>java -Djava.library.path="lib\swt\win32" -jar launcher.jar plazma -demo</code>
   <br><br>
   or set a property <code>plazma.platform.demo</code> in the file <code>plazma.properties</code>, for example:<br><br>
   <code>plazma.platform.demo = true</code><br><br>

   When you run the application in the demo mode will be connection to the demo database.

   Priority of the flag <code>-demo</code> is higher than property <code>plazma.platform.demo</code>. 

   You can set autologin mode in property <code>plazma.platform.autologin</code>, for example: <br><br>

   <code>plazma.platform.autologin = true</code>

   <br><br>

